message.content:
Statement to verify: In January 2020, Lucid Dreams was officially released as a single and given a video. It has since peaked at number three. Higgins released his first studio album, Goodbye & Good Riddance, on January 1, 2020. On January 1, 2020, he released a two-song EP, Too Soon..., in remembrance of and dedicated to deceased rappers Lil Peep and XXXTentacion, the latter of whom was killed in a homicide case relating to robbery a day earlier. The song Legends from that EP charted under its debut at number 65.

1. Can you provide evidence confirming the official release date of "Lucid Dreams" as a single and its peak position on the charts in January 2020?
2. Is there verifiable information supporting the claim that Juice WRLD released his first studio album, Goodbye & Good Riddance, on January 1, 2020?
3. Are there reliable sources confirming the release date of the two-song EP, Too Soon..., by Juice WRLD in January 2020 and its dedication to Lil Peep and XXXTentacion?
4. Can you establish a clear timeline of events surrounding the homicide case involving XXXTentacion and the subsequent release of the song "Legends" from the Too Soon... EP, including its chart performance at number 65?
